body:
Yeah. I did some cleanup recently to get conflicts between core & boringssl
cleaned up. We need to do another pass on c++ and core, but I haven't found
the time yet.

If there's any interest in cleaning it up, I'd be happy to post a tweaked
sanity test as a PR for someone to make it pass (it's mostly going to be
about renaming some files).

On Sun, Feb 28, 2016 at 11:19 AM Vijay Pai notifications@github.com wrote:

> This doesn't seem to break anything, but maybe is a sanity issue to
> consider? I saw this on my ancient home desktop iMac.
> 
> /Library/Developer/CommandLineTools/usr/bin/libtool: warning same member
> name (slice.o) in output file used for input files:
> /Users/vpai/Code/Git/grpc/objs/dbg/src/core/support/slice.o and:
> /Users/vpai/Code/Git/grpc/objs/dbg/src/cpp/util/slice.o (due to use of
> basename, truncation, blank padding or duplicate input files)
> /Library/Developer/CommandLineTools/usr/bin/libtool: warning same member
> name (time.o) in output file used for input files:
> /Users/vpai/Code/Git/grpc/objs/dbg/src/cpp/util/time.o and:
> /Users/vpai/Code/Git/grpc/objs/dbg/src/core/support/time.o (due to use of
> basename, truncation, blank padding or duplicate input files)
> 
> —
> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub
> https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/5473.

Like you mention, it doesn't hurt us yet, but it's certainly going to bite
at an unwanted point.
